This paper proposes a new deep recurrent neural network framework for visual sequence information processing, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) fields. The paper also introduces a new RNN module and a training scheme, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) fields. Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization and accuracy improvements of the proposed framework, which are relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) field.
